  <verse number="6" style="v" />An elder must be without blame, the husband of one wife, with faithful children not accused of being wicked or undisciplined.

  <verse number="7" style="v" />It is necessary for the overseer, as God's household manager, to be blameless. He must not be loud or unrestrained. He must not be easily angered, not addicted to wine, not a brawler, and not a greedy man.
